Um, the USA involvment in WW2 was a Military Strike with the declared motive to end a conflict. It is more comparable with recent US-Military activities in Bosnia, Sumalia, etc.. Actions which I still think are rightly motivated and still support, inspite of some mistakes in the actual execution of them.<br>
<br>
A Military Strike into the Mid, or Near-East the way it is called for by many People on this Board is one motivated out of the need for revenge and retribution, motives that should never be acted upon. Takin the Law into ones own hands is forbidden in all civilized nations for a reason.<br>
<br>
Personally I think we dont live in the World we did 55 years ago, but if you want to draw comparisons: Some out of Hitlers Legitimation for strikin out against Poland and Russia was, that those countries housed a large Jewish population, which in turn was blamed for the cowardly Assassination of Prince Franz Ferdinand and his Wife Spophie Chotek. Though at that Time never proven, german and other european newspapers where &quot;90% sure&quot; that this assassination was staged by Jews. With popular rhetoric, Hitler managed to blame just about everything from the weak Economy (Gas Prices anyone?) to the British &amp; American involvement into WW2 on the &quot;Jewish World Conspiracy&quot;.<br>
<br>
Democracy and Liberalism of the Weimarer Republic where set aside within a few years after that, just because one man was able to channel a peoples shock and hatred to his own ends.<br>
<br>
This is why we need to be ever watchful, outside and inside, never to let our humanistic Ideals slip, no matter how much we want to find a culprit, especially if our ethics are challenged in ways, such as the Attack on the WTC.<br>
<br>
Cause unlike the 1939 Germany, if we, the USA ever forget these Ideals, there is noone there to safe the World.<br>
<br>
